<poem>
  <phead>
    <ptitle>Sonnet 126</ptitle>
    <author>
      <first-name>William</first-name>
      <last-name>Shakespeare</last-name>
    </author>
  </phead>
  <pbody>
    <stanza>
      <line>O thou my lovely<phoneme category="a">power</phoneme><phoneme category="a">power</phoneme><phoneme category="a">power</phoneme><phoneme category="a">power</phoneme><phoneme category="a">power</phoneme></line>
      <line>Dost hold Time fickle glass<phoneme category="b">hour</phoneme><phoneme category="b">hour</phoneme><phoneme category="b">hour</phoneme></line>
      <line>Who hast by waning grown and therein<phoneme category="a">show</phoneme></line>
      <line>Thy lovers withering as thy sweet self<phoneme category="b">grow</phoneme></line>
      <line>If Nature sovereign mistress over<phoneme category="c">wrack</phoneme></line>
      <line>As thou goest onwards still will pluck thee<phoneme category="d">back</phoneme></line>
      <line>She keeps thee to this purpose that her<phoneme category="c">skill</phoneme></line>
      <line>May time disgrace and wretched minutes<phoneme category="d">kill</phoneme></line>
      <line>Yet fear her<phoneme category="e">pleasure</phoneme><phoneme category="e">pleasure</phoneme><phoneme category="e">pleasure</phoneme><phoneme category="e">pleasure</phoneme><phoneme category="e">pleasure</phoneme><phoneme category="e">pleasure</phoneme></line>
      <line>She may detain<phoneme category="f">treasure</phoneme><phoneme category="f">treasure</phoneme><phoneme category="f">treasure</phoneme><phoneme category="f">treasure</phoneme><phoneme category="f">treasure</phoneme><phoneme category="f">treasure</phoneme></line>
      <line>Her audit though delayed answered must<phoneme category="e">be</phoneme></line>
      <line>And her quietus is to render<phoneme category="f">thee</phoneme></line>
    </stanza>
  </pbody>
</poem>